## FILE SYSTEM RULES
- The project must use dynamic path detection instead of hardcoded paths to ensure folder rename compatibility.
- Use `os.path` for cross-platform path construction (Windows, macOS, Linux).
- Ensure path detection logic is consistent across all files.
- CSV file path should be detected using `src/core/csv_processor.py`.
- Excel file path should be detected using `src/core/excel_processor.py`.
- Driver path should be detected using `src/core/config.py`.
- Download folder path should be set in `src/core/config.py`.
- When detecting paths, go up from `src/core/` to `src/` to the project root.
- The default download folder is `~/Downloads/PO_Attachments`.
- In `src/core/csv_processor.py` and `src/core/excel_processor.py`, the path detection should go up from `src/core/` to `src/` to the project root by using `os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(current_dir))`.
- In `src/core/config.py`, the DRIVER_PATH detection should go up from `src/core/` to `src/` to the project root.

