## WINDOWS-SPECIFIC RULES

- When setting up the project on Windows, it is recommended to use the `install_windows.bat` installer.
- If Python is not found, ensure it is installed from [python.org](https://www.python.org/downloads/) and that "Add Python to PATH" is checked during installation.
- If encountering permission errors, run Command Prompt as Administrator or PowerShell as Administrator with execution policy set using `Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser`.
- If Edge browser issues occur, ensure Microsoft Edge is installed and up-to-date from [microsoft.com/edge](https://www.microsoft.com/edge).
- To troubleshoot virtual environment issues, remove the existing `venv` directory and recreate it.
- The Windows-ready package (`CoupaDownloads_Windows_v1.0.0.zip`) is a complete, self-contained package that includes an automatic EdgeDriver downloader, enhanced driver manager, one-click Windows installer (`setup_windows.bat`), all Python dependencies (`requirements.txt`), sample input files, and comprehensive documentation. **(Deprecated - now uses manual driver setup)**
- After downloading and extracting the `CoupaDownloads_Windows_v1.0.0.zip` package, run `setup_windows.bat`, edit `data\input\input.csv` with your PO numbers, activate the virtual environment using `venv\Scripts\activate`, and run the application using `python src\main.py`.
- If no drivers are found, run `download_drivers.bat` to download the required EdgeDrivers. **(Deprecated)**
- The Windows bundle is now created using `scripts/create_windows_bundle.py` which generates `output/CoupaDownloads_Windows_v1.0.0.zip`.

## PYINSTALLER RULES

- To build a single `.exe` file, use the `build_single_exe.py` script or the manual PyInstaller command: `pyinstaller --onefile --windowed src/main.py`. **(Deprecated)**
- The project includes security optimizations such as UPX compression, binary stripping, excluding unnecessary modules, and a custom manifest.
- The GUI integration includes a Tkinter interface, progress bars, and user-friendly error dialogs.
- The driver management includes embedded EdgeDrivers with automatic detection and fallback mechanisms. **(Deprecated - now handled manually)**
- To create a custom spec file, use `pyi-makespec src/main.py --onefile --windowed --name CoupaDownloads --icon=icon.ico` and build with `pyinstaller CoupaDownloads.spec`. **(Deprecated)**
- The output of PyInstaller builds is located in the `dist/` directory for the single EXE and the `build/` directory for build files.
- Ensure PyInstaller is installed using `pip install pyinstaller` before running build scripts or manual commands.

