## WEB DRIVER 138 BUNDLE RULES
- The Windows bundle should now include the actual EdgeDriver 138 as the default driver.
- The Windows bundle is created using `scripts/create_windows_bundle.py` which copies the EdgeDriver 138 executable to the `release/drivers` directory.
- The `release/drivers` directory should contain the following files:
    - `msedgedriver.exe` (EdgeDriver 138)
    - `msedgedriver_138.exe` (EdgeDriver 138)
    - `msedgedriver_120.exe` (EdgeDriver 138 - fallback)
    - `msedgedriver_119.exe` (EdgeDriver 138 - fallback)
    - `msedgedriver_118.exe` (EdgeDriver 138 - fallback)
    - `README.md` (WebDriver information)
    - `version_info.json` (Version information)
- The `setup_windows.bat` script should detect the real EdgeDriver 138 and confirm that no manual download is required.

- **Manual Webdriver Handling:** The project will no longer automatically download the webdriver. The webdriver `.exe` file will always be manually provided in the `drivers` directory.
- **All internal references must be checked and correct to build the Windows app.**
- **The Windows bundle creation script must be as assertive as possible.**
- **The most complete .exe must be produced as possible.**
- The Windows bundle is saved in `output/CoupaDownloads_Windows_v1.0.0.zip`.